docs.abstract: Ever been haunted by an online ad for an item you researched or bought? Targeted ads were designed to follow you around everywhere. Here’s how to banish them.
docs.snippet: Ever been haunted by an online ad for an item you researched or bought? Targeted ads were designed to follow you around everywhere. Here’s how to banish them.
docs.lead_paragraph: Online ads have always been annoying, but now they’re worse than ever.

headline.main: Are Targeted Ads Stalking You? Here’s How to Make Them Stop
headline.print_headline: Targeted Ads Stalking You? You Can Make Them Go Away

docs.abstract: Over 12 years in charge, Ms. Nooyi worked to diversify the company’s products away from decreasingly profitable sugary soft drinks.
docs.snippet: Over 12 years in charge, Ms. Nooyi worked to diversify the company’s products away from decreasingly profitable sugary soft drinks.
docs.lead_paragraph: In her 12 years as chief executive of PepsiCo, Indra K. Nooyi has been part of an elite club: She is one of only a small number of women leading large corporations. It is a position that has often meant her every move received greater scrutiny than the actions of her male peers.

headline.main: Indra Nooyi, PepsiCo C.E.O. Who Pushed for Healthier Products, to Step Down
headline.print_headline: As PepsiCo’s C.E.O. Plans Exit, Women’s Corporate Clout Fades

docs.abstract: Videos that start without your consent are prominent across the web. Our tech columnist explains how the industry got here and what we can do.
docs.snippet: Videos that start without your consent are prominent across the web. Our tech columnist explains how the industry got here and what we can do.
docs.lead_paragraph: The web is in a dark place, as I plan to examine in the next several columns. If you need proof, look no further than autoplay videos, the first example.

headline.main: Autoplay Videos Are Not Going Away. Here’s How to Fight Them.
headline.print_headline: Alas, Living With Those Ghastly Autoplay Videos

docs.abstract: The index has fallen as much as 10 percent in a year of trade wars and collapsing currencies, but with big American companies making lots of money, the long bull market keeps going.
docs.snippet: The index has fallen as much as 10 percent in a year of trade wars and collapsing currencies, but with big American companies making lots of money, the long bull market keeps going.
docs.lead_paragraph: For much of the year, the stock market has been on the ropes. Trade wars have erupted, the Federal Reserve raised rates, emerging market currencies collapsed, and major technology firms faced regulatory scrutiny — and, in the case of Amazon, presidential broadsides via messages on Twitter. Investors quailed at times, sending stocks down by as much as 10 percent.

headline.main: S.&P. Closes at a Record, as Profits Defy Turmoil
headline.print_headline: Basking in a Sweet Spot, Markets Disregard Turmoil

docs.abstract: Thanks to the way Google processes your mail, you can modify part of your address for different situations and still get all your messages.

docs.lead_paragraph: Q. Do periods matter in Gmail addresses? I get messages addressed to my account at firstnamelastname@gmail.com but also to firstname.lastname@gmail.com, and none of these seem to be meant for other people.

headline.main: Make Several Gmail Addresses Out of One

docs.abstract: The TV operator said it would sell off two stations through an independent trust. That was not enough to satisfy the Federal Communications Commission chairman’s concerns.
docs.snippet: The TV operator said it would sell off two stations through an independent trust. That was not enough to satisfy the Federal Communications Commission chairman’s concerns.
docs.lead_paragraph: Sinclair Broadcast Group, the largest local television operator in the United States, tried to placate federal regulators on Wednesday regarding its proposal to buy a rival TV group. But the Federal Communications Commission still voted unanimously to have a judge review aspects of the deal, a potentially ominous sign for the merger.

headline.main: Sinclair Tries to Appease F.C.C., but Its Tribune Bid Is Challenged
headline.print_headline: Sinclair Alters Tribune Bid, but F.C.C. Orders Review
